<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Genbel half yr shr dips, div up.</title>
<headline>Genbel half yr shr dips, div up.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-02-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended December 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, headline (cts)   54   vs 59</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 20   vs 15</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   20   vs 257</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   21   vs 263</p>
<p>    Tax			 1    vs 6</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   none vs 66</p>
<p>    Revenue		   30   vs 345</p>
<p>Div payable: March 20</p>
<p>On register: March 7</p>
<p>Full name: Genbel South Africa Limited</p>
<p>NOTE - The restructuring of the group and the distribution of its portfolio to electing shareholders in May 1996 also resulted in a reduction in the company's issued share capital from 434.6 million shares to the current 37.9 million shares, the company said.</p>
<p>Consequently comparisons between gross figures in the financial statement were misleading.</p>
<p>'Per share' comparisons were, however, valid.</p>
<p>The company said it should again report positive returns in the second half of the year provided South African equity markets did not deteriorate markedly from current levels.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
